5.  The Mumuye can be found in ____________ state. (a) Adamawa (b) Taraba (c) Bauchi  

6.  ____________is an example of a town where majorly Okun people can be found. (a) Kaaba (b) Lagos (c) Jalingo 

7.  The traditional occupation of Fulani men is _____________ (a) Farming (b) Fishing (c) Cattle rearing  

8.  _____________ is a cultural festival of the Ibibio. (a) Egungun (b) New yam (c) Ekpe  

9.  The language spoken by the Igala is _______________(a) Efik (b) Igala (c) Hausa  

10.  The _____________ people can be found in towns like Oturkpo, Owukpa and Ogboju. (a) Idoma (b) Igala (c) Fulani  

11.  The Kalabari's people's favourite food include ____________ and fisherman soup (a) Onunu (b) Isiewu (c) Afang  

12.  Who was the founder of Opobo kingdom? (a) Ladi Kwali (b) King Jaja (c) Oba Ovonramwen  

13.  A female hero is called _____________ (a) Heroine (b) Heroess (c) Herower  

14.  Who designed the Nigerian flag? (a) Mary Williams (b) Pa Michael Taiwo Akinkunmi (c) Mary's Lessor ssor  

15.  Jaja of Opobo was the leader of the ____________ (a) Benin city (b) Abuja (c) Opobo kingdom  

16.  Nigeria has many heroes and heroines who have made Nigeria proud through their contributions. (a) True (b) False  

17.  The early heros are dead while some of the modern heroes are still alive. (a) True (b) False  

18.  Who died in 1891 on his way back from Britain where he was forcefully taken to? (a) Pa Michael Taiwo Akinkunmi (b) Oba Ovonramwen Nogbaisi of Benin (c) King Jaja of Opobo  

19.  According to the material, Opobo kingdom is now part of the modern Rivers State. (a) True (b) False  

20.  Who made figurative patterned pots of different shapes and sizes using her creative ability? (a) Mary's lessor (b) Hajiya Ladi Kwali (c) Margaret Ekpo  

21.  Oba Ovonramwen was born in ____________ (a) 1995 (b) 1888 (c) 1857 

22.  _____________ people enjoyed economic prosperity during Oba Ovonramwen's reign. (a) Benin (b) Sokoto (c) Enugu  

23.  _____________ was regarded as the best Nigerian potter before her death. (a) Margaret Ekpo (b) Funmilayo Kuti (c) Lady Kwali  

24.  The only Nigerian woman whose picture is on a Nigerian naira currency note is _______________________ (a) Ladi Kwali (b) Queen Amina (c) Queen Moremi  

25.  Hajiya Ladi Kwali was born in 1925 in _____________ (a) Lagos (b) Gwari (c) Abuja  

26.  According to the material, who was the member of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire (MBE)? (a) Pa Michael Taiwo Akinkunmi (b) King Jaja of Opobo (c) Ladi Kwali  

27.  According to the material, his people produced artistic works like bronze, decorated brass, ornamental ivory and so on. What is the material refer to? (a) King Jaja of Opobo (b) Oba Ovonramwen (c) Pa Michael Taiwo Akinkunmi  

28.  The Abuja pottery was renamed the Ladi Kwali pottery to honor _____________ (a) President Bola Ahmed Tinubu (b) President Good-luck Jonathan (c) Ladi Kwali  

29.  A hero is usually a noble and someone who has special qualities like courage, love, honesty, patriotism, etc. (a) True (b) False  

30.  A hero usually fights for the benefits of his people or community. (a) True (b) False  

